 will prove useful for future typological research. This handbook will provide an essential reference for both advanced students and researchers in word-formation and related fields within linguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxMorphology. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxWord formation. 4aWord-Formation, Morphology, Language Typology, European Languages. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aMüller, Peter O., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOhnheiser, Ingeborg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlsen, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRainer, Franz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2015z9783110439670oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2016z9783110485196oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2018z9783110548280oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2019z9783110621044oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103946890 cprintz978311024626140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311024627840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110246278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110246278.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEB